## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of up-to-date and comprehensive data on the death penalty. The arguments presented are based on the most recent and relevant sources available, but the dynamic nature of legal and ethical debates means that perspectives and policies can change rapidly. Additionally, the report focuses on arguments in favor of the death penalty and does not address the extensive arguments against it, which are equally significant in the broader debate.